docs.lead_paragraph: The United States Mail Steamer Ohio, HENRY K. DAVENPORT, U. S. N., Commander, arrived at noon yesterday, from Aspinwall via Kingston, Ja., with three bundred passengers, the California mails of the 31st July, two millions and thirty thousand dollars in gold dust on freight, and five hundred thousand dollars additional estimated in the hands of passengers.

docs.lead_paragraph: Our files of Panama papers are to the 17th of August. FRANCIS W. RICE, U. S. Consul at Acapulco, having obtained leave of absence, was at Panama on a visit. The ship Monde is being fitted up at Panama, for the use of the American Hospital Society.
